cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the task of semantic segmentation in medical imaging and instance segmentation in natural images. The use of a U-Net architecture is also a common approach in computer vision tasks. 

The paper also involves the use of a conditional variational auto-encoder (cVAE) for modeling the hierarchical latent space decomposition, which suggests that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. 

The paper's focus on learning complex structured distributions across scales and separating independent factors across scales could also place it in the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-categories. 

Finally, the paper's use of natural language processing techniques for structured output prediction tasks beyond segmentation could also place it in the computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category.
